Here's an updated design and code for the microcontroller to include a speed control potentiometer and a forward/reverse switch for direction control, as well as over-temperature and over-current protection and a display for showing motor direction and speed.

Design:

* AC to DC conversion: KBPC5010 bridge rectifier, 4700uF capacitor, and 5V voltage regulator
* H-bridge: DRV8412 dual full-bridge motor driver
* Microcontroller: Teensy 4.1
* Potentiometer: 10K ohm
* Forward/reverse switch: DPDT
* Display: 16x2 LCD

